# Writer Skill — User Extensions (EXTEND.md)

This file personalizes the writer skill for one user or one project. It
overrides the defaults in `SKILL.md` (Audience Profile, Voice & Style,
platform preferences, etc.).

## Where to put this file

| Path | Scope | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| `<cwd>/.writer-skill/EXTEND.md` | Project-level | Team-shared config, or a specific publication with its own voice |
| `~/.writer-skill/EXTEND.md` | User-level | Your personal default voice across all projects |

If both exist, the project-level file wins.

## What the skill does with this file

At the start of every writing session (before Phase 1), the skill reads
this file in full and treats it as additional context. Directives below
override the defaults in `SKILL.md`. **The user is not prompted about
this** — personalization is silent.

## Full schema (all fields optional)

Copy the block below to your own EXTEND.md and keep only the keys you
actually want to override. Unused keys fall back to the defaults in
SKILL.md.

```yaml
# Version pin — increment when the schema changes so old files still work
version: 1

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Audience & Voice
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Replaces the default "young curious reader" Audience Profile.
# Write a natural-language paragraph; the skill consumes it as-is.
target_reader: |
  AI PM 求职者、创业者、产品思辨爱好者。懂产品也懂技术，
  对学术腔有抗体，爱看"有判断"的内容。会转发那些能当成社交货币
  的观点文（"原来是这样"），但讨厌鸡汤和空话。

# Files the skill reads at the start of Phase 3 as voice anchors.
# Give 1-3 articles where your voice comes through strongest.
# Paths can be absolute or relative to the cwd at write time.
# PURELY for style — sentence rhythm, word choice, transitions.
style_samples:
  - /Users/you/Writing/我的代表作-1.md
  - /Users/you/Writing/我的代表作-2.md

# Your own content material — learning notes, war stories, project logs,
# curated references. Read in Phase 2 BEFORE general WebSearch, as
# first-class source material. Phase 6's source-auditor role checks how
# well these got used in the draft.
#
# Each source takes a path + type. Path can be file or directory.
# Types:
#   - learning_notes: your notes from books/courses/talks
#   - war_stories: your own hands-on 踩坑 / experience logs
#   - reference: curated quotes, stats, frameworks you return to
content_sources:
  - path: /Users/you/Writing/学习笔记/
    type: learning_notes
  - path: /Users/you/Writing/踩坑本.md
    type: war_stories

# Words this user actively avoids. Appended to SKILL.md's default ban list
# (赋能、抓手、闭环 ...), not replacing it.
banned_phrases:
  - 心智
  - 打法
  - 赛道
  - 范式
  - 底层能力

# Words or patterns this user naturally uses. Use these as grace notes —
# mirror them where they fit, never force.
preferred_phrases:
  - 较劲
  - 落地
  - 踩过
  - 直接
  - "不是 X，是 Y"  # a rhetorical pattern

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Workflow defaults
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# The user's usual publish target. Skip the "which platform?" question
# in Phase 4 and go straight to formatting. User can still override by
# mentioning a different platform.
default_platform: wechat  # wechat | zhihu | xiaohongshu | substack | other

# Word-count target range. Overrides the default 1500-2500.
default_word_count: [1200, 2000]

# If true, the skill starts in Auto Plan Mode by default:
# presents a full execution plan, user approves once, then skill auto-runs
# Phases 2-6 and delivers all artifacts at the end.
# User can say "一步一步来" to exit auto mode mid-session.
quick_mode_default: false

# Opt out of the default Chinese casual phrase pool.
# When false (default), skill will naturally mix in phrases from
# references/chinese_casual_phrases.md (转场/判断/自嘲/情绪/拉近 categories)
# alongside your own preferred_phrases.
# Set to true if you write in an academic / cold / highly idiosyncratic
# voice and don't want default casual warmth injected.
disable_default_casual_phrases: false

# If true, Phase 4 WeChat formatting automatically runs
# `python -m scripts.render_wechat <slug>-wechat.md --open`
# after generating the markdown, opening the HTML preview.
auto_render_wechat: true

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional: custom reviewer roles (advanced)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Add extra reviewer prompts to Phase 5. Each file must live in roles/
# and follow the same format as the 5 built-in roles. Include the role
# name (filename without .md) here to include it in run_review.py's
# parallel review.
extra_reviewers: []
  # - ethics-checker
  # - seo-optimizer
```

## Minimum viable example

If you just want to lock in your voice without fiddling with other
settings, this is enough:

```yaml
version: 1
style_samples:
  - /Users/you/Writing/最能代表我声音的那篇.md
default_platform: wechat
```

## How the skill uses each field

**`target_reader`** → Read at the start of every phase. Every drafting
and reviewing decision filters through "would this bore *this* reader?"

**`style_samples`** → Read in full at the start of Phase 3. Claude matches
sentence length, paragraph rhythm, opening strategies, punctuation habits,
transitional phrases. This is the single highest-leverage setting —
prose style is hard to describe but easy to mirror.

**`banned_phrases` / `preferred_phrases`** → Cross-checked after every
drafting pass. Banned words are replaced; preferred patterns are
introduced where they fit naturally, never shoehorned.

**`default_platform` + `default_word_count`** → Skip upfront clarifying
questions. User can always say "actually make it a Zhihu answer" to
override mid-session.

**`quick_mode_default` + `auto_render_wechat`** → For high-volume writers
who've stopped needing guard rails. Everything still works, just with
fewer pauses.

**`extra_reviewers`** → Register additional roles for Phase 5 multi-role
review. Each referenced role name must have a matching file at
`roles/<name>.md`. `run_review.py` auto-discovers these.

## Not supported in v1 (future additions)

- Custom platforms beyond the built-in four (wechat/zhihu/xiaohongshu/substack)
- Per-platform voice variants (same article, different tones)
- Automated loading of memory from other Claude skills

If you need any of these, open an issue or file a PR.
